headline.main: YELLOW FEVER.; Contributions Still Coming in--New Cases of the Fever--Attacks on Shipboard. The telegraph brings the following up to last night:

docs.lead_paragraph: There were forty-eight deaths at Norfolk during the 24 hours ending at noon, Thursday. At Portsmouth, during the same period, there were only eleven deaths. There was a considerable diminution in the number of new cases, especially in Portsmouth.
